nian reformers taking the Oslo Accords as an occasion to resume normal political life. Providing a clear and urgently needed vantage point on most of the issues of Palestinian reform and governance that have emerged in recent policy debates—issues such as corruption, constitutionalism, democracy, and rule of law—Brown’s book helps to put Palestinian aspirations and accomplishments in their proper context within a long and complex history and within the larger Arab world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNation-state. 0aPalestinian ArabsxPolitics and governmentx1993-. 0aPalestinian ArabsxPolitics and governmenty1993- 0aPalestinian ArabsxPolitics and governmenty1993-. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aarab israeli conflict.  aarab national models.  aarab palestine.  aarab world.  aconstitutionalism.  afieldwork.  ahistorical.  ahistory buffs.  ainsider perspective.  ainterviews.  alegal development.  amiddle east.  anation building.  anonfiction.  aoslo accords.  apalestine.  apalestinian legislative council.  apalestinian politics.  apalestinian reformers.  apolitical perspective.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  asocial activists.  atextbooks.  aworld politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093778940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937789423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937789/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles